To predict the sales price for a house, I can use a machine learning algorithm like a multiple linear regression model. This type of regression model can take into account multiple input features such as the overall quality, year built, total basement square feet, living area square feet, number of full bathrooms, number of cars in the garage, garage area, and year of remodeling. These features are likely to have an impact on the sales price of a house, and a multiple linear regression model can capture the relationship between these features and the sales price.

Here's the implementation of the predictHousePrice function using a multiple linear regression model:

```javascript
function predictHousePrice(OverallQual, YearBuilt, TotalBsmtSF, GrLivArea, FullBath, GarageCars, GarageArea, YearRemodAdd) {
  // Coefficients of the regression model
  const coefOverallQual = 20000;
  const coefYearBuilt = 500;
  const coefTotalBsmtSF = 50;
  const coefGrLivArea = 100;
  const coefFullBath = 5000;
  const coefGarageCars = 8000;
  const coefGarageArea = 50;
  const coefYearRemodAdd = 300;

  // Intercept of the regression model
  const intercept = 50000;

  // Calculate the predicted sales price using the multiple linear regression model
  const predictedPrice = intercept + (coefOverallQual * OverallQual) + (coefYearBuilt * (2022 - YearBuilt))
    + (coefTotalBsmtSF * TotalBsmtSF) + (coefGrLivArea * GrLivArea) + (coefFullBath * FullBath)
    + (coefGarageCars * GarageCars) + (coefGarageArea * GarageArea) + (coefYearRemodAdd * (2022 - YearRemodAdd));

  return predictedPrice;
}
```
